// ============================================================================
// Key Points for AI
// ============================================================================

/**
 * When generating responses, the AI should:
 *
 * 1. Always use "version": "advanced-v1" to trigger the interpreter
 * 2. Use high-level commands (wave, symmetry, cascade, etc.) instead of individual events
 * 3. Provide clear descriptions for each command
 * 4. Match shell names to the theme (Red/Gold for national, Pink/Purple for romantic, Blue/Cyan for tech)
 * 5. Use appropriate patterns:
 *    - "open_wings" for grand openings
 *    - "close_in" for dramatic closings
 *    - "left_to_right" / "right_to_left" for sweeping effects
 * 6. Include an assistantMessage explaining the design choices
 * 7. Add notes about the theme and structure
 *
 * The interpreter will handle:
 * - Calculating exact firing times
 * - Determining which tubes to fire
 * - Creating symmetric pairs
 * - Generating wave sequences
 * - All the complex math and logic
 *
 * This allows the AI to focus on artistic intent rather than technical details!
 */
